e 141: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement session management HTTP handlers\n  Line 420:   - Add session management section\n  Line 424: - [ ] **DOC-006**: Verify `pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md` is complete\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md:\n  Line 1: # Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n  Line 5: This document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n  Line 41: ├── session/                       # NEW: Session management package\n  Line 189:     // Enable session management\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-010: Router 会话管理\n  Line 5: This proposal defines the session management implementation for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The session management system is responsible for:\n  Line 13: The session management system enables stateful communication with agent runtimes and code interpreters, ensuring that related requests are routed to the same sandbox instance.\n  Line 56: - WebSocket session management (deferred to future AR)\n  Line 103: - No session state management overhead\n  Line 115: Delegate session management to clients; router only forwards session ID.\n  Line 128: **Decision:** Rejected. Server-side session management provides better observability, cleanup, and lifecycle control.\n  Line 356: 3. Document session management API\n  Line 399: 1. **WebSocket Support** - Extend session management for WebSocket connections\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/README.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n  Line 9: Implement session management functionality for the pkg/router module.\n  Line 14: - [ ] Design session management architecture\n  Line 16: - [ ] Implement session lifecycle management\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/status.json:\n  Line 2:   \"ar\": \"AR-010\",\n  Line 3:   \"title\": \"Router 会话管理\",\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 366: 1. Should the router support WebSocket connections? (Deferred to AR-010)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/proposal.md:\n  Line 169: - No centralized session management\n  Line 175: **Decision:** Rejected. Router provides essential abstraction layer for session management, security, and lifecycle tracking.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md:\n  Line 59: - Webhook admission controllers (deferred to AR-010)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md:\n  Line 294:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"","metadata":{"matches":39,"truncated":false},"title":"AR-010|会话管理|session.*management","time":{"start":1775850891318,"end":1775850891337}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775850891376,"sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","part":{"id":"prt_d78f6284d001cMFdFbPNeBFeaA","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78f615a5001O2VvOmzImOCokM","sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":15601,"input":6,"output":142,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":53,"read":15400}},"cost":0}}
