{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850898251,"sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","part":{"id":"prt_d78f6337c001IljxnCbkAokFxD","messageID":"msg_d78f62898001Eo556jQCCue6l3","sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9e5c21fda20b444bad46192d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Functional Requirements\n10: \n11: 1. **Session Creation**: Create a new session when a client makes the first request to a backend\n12: 2. **Session Tracking**: Track active sessions per backend (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n13: 3. **Session Binding**: Bind client requests to specific backend instances based on session affinity\n14: 4. **Session Timeout**: Enforce session timeout policies (idle timeout, max duration)\n15: 5. **Session Cleanup**: Clean up expired or abandoned sessions\n16: 6. **Session Metrics**: Expose metrics for active sessions, session creation rate, etc.\n17: \n18: ### Non-Functional Requirements\n19: \n20: 1. **Performance**: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99\n21: 2. **Scalability**: Support 10,000+ concurrent sessions\n22: 3. **Reliability**: Session data persisted in Redis for recovery\n23: 4. **Thread Safety**: Safe concurrent access from multiple goroutines\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ### Component Structure\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pkg/router/\n31: ├── router.go                      # Main router implementation\n32: ├── router_test.go                 # Unit tests\n33: ├── handler.go                     # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n34: ├── handler_test.go                # Handler tests\n35: ├── resolver.go                    # Route resolution logic\n36: ├── resolver_test.go               # Resolver tests\n37: ├── health.go                      # Health check manager\n38: ├── health_test.go                 # Health check tests\n39: ├── config.go                      # Configuration structures\n40: ├── types.go                       # Type definitions\n41: ├── session/                       # NEW: Session management package\n42: │   ├── manager.go                 # Session manager implementation\n43: │   ├── manager_test.go            # Manager tests\n44: │   ├── session.go                 # Session data structure\n45: │   ├── session_test.go            # Session tests\n46: │   ├── store.go                   # Session storage interface\n47: │   ├── store_test.go              # Store tests\n48: │   ├── redis_store.go             # Redis-backed session store\n49: │   ├── redis_store_test.go        # Redis store tests\n50: │   ├── memory_store.go            # In-memory session store (dev/test)\n51: │   ├── memory_store_test.go       # Memory store tests\n52: │   └── config.go                  # Session configuration\n53: └── middleware/                    # NEW: HTTP middleware\n54:     ├── session_middleware.go      # Session extraction/attachment\n55:     ├── session_middleware_test.go # Middleware tests\n56:     └── auth_middleware.go         # Authentication middleware\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Integration Points\n60: \n61: - **Session Store**: Redis (production) or in-memory (dev/test) for session persistence\n62: - **Clientset**: Uses generated `versioned.Clientset` for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n63: - **Informers**: Watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources\n64: - **Existing Router**: Extends AR-009 router with session-aware routing\n65: \n66: ### High-Level Flow\n67: \n68: ```\n69: ┌─────────────┐\n70: │   Client    │\n71: └──────┬──────┘\n72:        │ HTTP Request (with/without session token)\n73:        ▼\n74: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n75: │   Session Middleware            │\n76: │   - Extract session token       │\n77: │   - Validate session            │\n78: │   - Attach to context           │\n79: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n80:                │\n81:                ▼\n82: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n83: │   Handler                       │\n84: │   - Check session affinity      │\n85: │   - Resolve backend             │\n86: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n87:                │\n88:                ▼\n89: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n90: │   Session Manager               │\n91: │   - Get/Create session          │\n92: │   - Update last activity        │\n93: │   - Bind to backend             │\n94: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n95:                │\n96:                ▼\n97: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n98: │   Resolver                      │\n99: │   - Look up route entry         │\n100: │   - Apply session affinity      │\n101: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n102:                │\n103:                ▼\n104: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n105: │   Backend (AgentRuntime/CI)     │\n106: │   - Proxy request               │\n107: └─────────────────────────────────┘\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Session Lifecycle\n111: \n112: ```\n113: ┌──────────────┐\n114: │   Created    │ (first request or explicit creation)\n115: └──────┬───────┘\n116:        │\n117:        ▼\n118: ┌──────────────┐\n119: │   Active     │ (requests being processed)\n120: └──────┬───────┘\n121:        │\n122:        ├─ Idle Timeout ──▶ ┌──────────────┐\n123:        │                   │   Expired    │\n124:        ├─ Max Duration ──▶ └──────┬───────┘\n125:        │                          │\n126:        ▼                          ▼\n127: ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐\n128: │  Terminated  │◀─────────│  Cleanup     │\n129: └──────────────┘  (delete) └──────────────┘\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Data Structures\n133: \n134: ### Session\n135: \n136: ```go\n137: type Session struct {\n138:     // Unique session identifier\n139:     ID string `json:\"id\"`\n140:     \n141:     // Namespace of the backend resource\n142:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n143:     \n144:     // Backend kind: \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n145:     Kind string `json:\"kind\"`\n146:     \n147:     // Name of the backend resource\n148:     BackendName string `json:\"backendName\"`\n149:     \n150:     // Backend URL for routing\n151:     BackendURL string `json:\"backendURL\"`\n152:     \n153:     // User identifier (from auth token or request header)\n154:     UserID string `json:\"userId\"`\n155:     \n156:     // Session creation time\n157:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n158:     \n159:     // Last activity timestamp\n160:     LastActivityAt time.Time `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n161:     \n162:     // Session expiration time (CreatedAt + MaxDuration)\n163:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n164:     \n165:     // Session state\n166:     State SessionState `json:\"state\"`\n167:     \n168:     // Metadata for extensibility\n169:     Metadata map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n170:     \n171:     // Lock for concurrent access\n172:     mu sync.RWMutex\n173: }\n174: \n175: type SessionState string\n176: \n177: const (\n178:     SessionStateActive     SessionState = \"Active\"\n179:     SessionStateIdle       SessionState = \"Idle\"\n180:     SessionStateExpired    SessionState = \"Expired\"\n181:     SessionStateTerminated SessionState = \"Terminated\"\n182: )\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ### SessionConfig\n186: \n187: ```go\n188: type SessionConfig struct {\n189:     // Enable session management\n190:     Enabled bool\n191:     \n192:     // Session cookie name\n193:     CookieName string\n194:     \n195:     // Session cookie domain (optional)\n196:     CookieDomain string\n197:     \n198:     // Session cookie path\n199:     CookiePath string\n200:     \n201:     // Session cookie secure flag\n202:     CookieSecure bool\n203:     \n204:     // Session cookie HTTP-only flag\n205:     CookieHTTPOnly bool\n206:     \n207:     // Session cookie SameSite policy\n208:     CookieSameSite http.SameSite\n209:     \n210:     // Session token header name\n211:     TokenHeader string\n212:     \n213:     // Maximum session duration\n214:     MaxDuration time.Duration\n215:     \n216:     // Idle session timeout\n217:     IdleTimeout time.Duration\n218:     \n219:     // Session cleanup interval\n220:     CleanupInterval time.Duration\n221:     \n222:     // Store type: \"redis\" or \"memory\"\n223:     StoreType string\n224:     \n225:     // Redis configuration\n226:     Redis RedisSessionConfig\n227: }\n228: \n229: type RedisSessionConfig struct {\n230:     // Redis address\n231:     Addr string\n232:     \n233:     // Redis password\n234:     Password string\n235:     \n236:     // Redis database number\n237:     DB int\n238:     \n239:     // Session key prefix\n240:     KeyPrefix string\n241:     \n242:     // Connection pool size\n243:     PoolSize int\n244:     \n245:     // Connection timeout\n246:     DialTimeout time.Duration\n247:     \n248:     // Read timeout\n249:     ReadTimeout time.Duration\n250:     \n251:     // Write timeout\n252:     WriteTimeout time.Duration\n253: }\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### SessionManager\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: type SessionManager struct {\n260:     config    *SessionConfig\n261:     store     SessionStore\n262:     metrics   *SessionMetrics\n263:     stopCh    chan struct{}\n264:     wg        sync.WaitGroup\n265:     mu        sync.RWMutex\n266: }\n267: \n268: type SessionStore interface {\n269:     // Get retrieves a session by ID\n270:     Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n271:     \n272:     // Set stores or updates a session\n273:     Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n274:     \n275:     // Delete removes a session\n276:     Delete(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n277:     \n278:     // List returns sessions matching namespace and kind\n279:     List(ctx context.Context, namespace, kind string) ([]*Session, error)\n280:     \n281:     // ListByUser returns sessions for a specific user\n282:     ListByUser(ctx context.Context, userID string) ([]*Session, error)\n283:     \n284:     // Close closes the store connection\n285:     Close() error\n286: }\n287: \n288: type SessionMetrics struct {\n289:     ActiveSessions   prometheus.Gauge\n290:     SessionsCreated  prometheus.Counter\n291:     SessionsExpired  prometheus.Counter\n292:     SessionsTerminated prometheus.Counter\n293:     SessionDuration  prometheus.Histogram\n294:     StoreLatency     prometheus.Histogram\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### SessionMiddleware\n299: \n300: ```go\n301: type SessionMiddleware struct {\n302:     manager *SessionManager\n303:     config  *SessionConfig\n304: }\n305: \n306: // ExtractSession extracts session from request\n307: func (m *SessionMiddleware) ExtractSession(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n308: \n309: // AttachSession attaches session to response\n310: func (m *SessionMiddleware) AttachSession(w http.ResponseWriter, session *Session)\n311: \n312: // WithSession wraps handler with session context\n313: func (m *SessionMiddleware) WithSession(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ## API Contracts\n317: \n318: ### Session Token Format\n319: \n320: **Cookie-based (default):**\n321: ```\n322: Set-Cookie: agentcube_session=<session-id>; Path=/; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict\n323: ```\n324: \n325: **Header-based (alternative):**\n326: ```\n327: X-AgentCube-Session: <session-id>\n328: ```\n329: \n330: **JWT Payload (optional, for auth integration):**\n331: ```json\n332: {\n333:   \"sub\": \"user-123\",\n334:   \"sid\": \"session-abc\",\n335:   \"nss\": \"default\",\n336:   \"bk\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n337:   \"bkn\": \"my-runtime\",\n338:   \"iat\": 1699000000,\n339:   \"exp\": 1699086400\n340: }\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ### Session Endpoints\n344: \n345: The router exposes management endpoints for session operations:\n346: \n347: ```\n348: GET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n349:        - List all active sessions\n350:        - Query params: namespace, kind, userId\n351: \n352: GET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n353:        - Get session details\n354: \n355: DELETE /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n356:        - Terminate a session\n357: \n358: POST   /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n359:        - Create a new session (explicit)\n360:        - Body: { \"namespace\", \"kind\", \"backendName\", \"userId\" }\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ### Session Management Interface\n364: \n365: ```go\n366: type SessionManagerInterface interface {\n367:     // CreateSession creates a new session\n368:     CreateSession(ctx context.Context, req *CreateSessionRequest) (*Session, error)\n369:     \n370:     // GetSession retrieves a session by ID\n371:     GetSession(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n372:     \n373:     // UpdateSession updates session metadata\n374:     UpdateSession(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n375:     \n376:     // DeleteSession terminates and removes a session\n377:     DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n378:     \n379:     // ListSessions returns sessions matching filters\n380:     ListSessions(ctx context.Context, filters *SessionFilters) ([]*Session, error)\n381:     \n382:     // CleanupExpiredSessions removes expired sessions\n383:     CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n384:     \n385:     // Start starts the session manager background tasks\n386:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n387:     \n388:     // Shutdown gracefully stops the session manager\n389:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n390: }\n391: \n392: type CreateSessionRequest struct {\n393:     Namespace   string\n394:     Kind        string\n395:     BackendName string\n396:     BackendURL  string\n397:     UserID      string\n398:     Metadata    map[string]string\n399: }\n400: \n401: type SessionFilters struct {\n402:     Namespace string\n403:     Kind      string\n404:     UserID    string\n405:     State     SessionState\n406: }\n407: ```\n408: \n409: ### Resolve with Session Affinity\n410: \n411: **Modified Resolve Operation:**\n412: \n413: ```go\n414: // ResolveWithSession resolves route considering session affinity\n415: func (r *Resolver) ResolveWithSession(\n416:     ctx context.Context,\n417:     req *http.Request,\n418:     session *Session,\n419: ) (*RouteEntry, error)\n420: ```\n421: \n422: **Behavior:**\n423: 1. If session exists and is bound to a backend → return that backend\n424: 2. If session exists but backend is unhealthy → reassign to healthy backend\n425: 3. If no session → select backend using load balancing strategy\n426: 4. Update session's LastActivityAt timestamp\n427: \n428: ## Error Handling\n429: \n430: ### Error Types\n431: \n432: ```go\n433: var (\n434:     // Session errors\n435:     ErrSessionNotFound      = errors.New(\"session not found\")\n436:     ErrSessionExpired       = errors.New(\"session has expired\")\n437:     ErrSessionTerminated    = errors.New(\"session was terminated\")\n438:     ErrSessionCreateFailed  = errors.New(\"failed to create session\")\n439:     ErrSessionStoreError    = errors.New(\"session store error\")\n440:     \n441:     // Session affinity errors\n442:     ErrBackendUnavailable   = errors.New(\"backend unavailable for session\")\n443:     ErrAffinityBroken       = errors.New(\"session affinity cannot be maintained\")\n444:     \n445:     // Configuration errors\n446:     ErrInvalidSessionConfig = errors.New(\"invalid session configuration\")\n447:     ErrRedisConnectionFailed = errors.New(\"failed to connect to redis\")\n448: )\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Error Response Format\n452: \n453: ```go\n454: type SessionErrorResponse struct {\n455:     Error       string            `json:\"error\"`\n456:     Code        string            `json:\"code\"`\n457:     SessionID   string            `json:\"sessionId,omitempty\"`\n458:     Details     map[string]string `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n459:     Timestamp   string            `json:\"timestamp\"`\n460: }\n461: \n462: // Error codes\n463: const (\n464:     ErrCodeSessionNotFound      = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n465:     ErrCodeSessionExpired       = \"SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n466:     ErrCodeSessionTerminated    = \"SESSION_TERMINATED\"\n467:     ErrCodeBackendUnavailable   = \"BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE\"\n468:     ErrCodeAffinityBroken       = \"AFFINITY_BROKEN\"\n469: )\n470: ```\n471: \n472: ### Session Recovery Strategy\n473: \n474: | Scenario | Action |\n475: |----------|--------|\n476: | Session not found | Create new session, return 201 |\n477: | Session expired | Clean up, create new session |\n478: | Backend unhealthy | Reassign to healthy backend (if allowed) |\n479: | Redis connection lost | Fall back to memory store (if configured) |\n480: | Session store error | Log error, continue with degraded mode |\n481: \n482: ### Graceful Degradation\n483: \n484: ```go\n485: type FallbackStrategy string\n486: \n487: const (\n488:     FallbackMemory FallbackStrategy = \"memory\" // Use in-memory store\n489:     FallbackDirect FallbackStrategy = \"direct\" // Direct routing without sessions\n490:     FallbackReject FallbackStrategy = \"reject\" // Reject requests\n491: )\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ## Testing Strategy\n495: \n496: ### Unit Tests\n497: \n498: **File**: `session/manager_test.go`\n499: \n500: ```go\n501: func TestSessionManager_CreateSession(t *testing.T)\n502: func TestSessionManager_GetSession(t *testing.T)\n503: func TestSessionManager_DeleteSession(t *testing.T)\n504: func TestSessionManager_ListSessions(t *testing.T)\n505: func TestSessionManager_CleanupExpiredSessions(t *testing.T)\n506: func TestSessionManager_SessionAffinity(t *testing.T)\n507: func TestSessionManager_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n508: ```\n509: \n510: **File**: `session/session_test.go`\n511: \n512: ```go\n513: func TestSession_IsExpired(t *testing.T)\n514: func TestSession_IsIdle(t *testing.T)\n515: func TestSession_UpdateActivity(t *testing.T)\n516: func TestSession_MarshalJSON(t *testing.T)\n517: func TestSession_ThreadSafety(t *testing.T)\n518: ```\n519: \n520: **File**: `session/redis_store_test.go`\n521: \n522: ```go\n523: func TestRedisStore_GetSet(t *testing.T)\n524: func TestRedisStore_Delete(t *testing.T)\n525: func TestRedisStore_List(t *testing.T)\n526: func TestRedisStore_ListByUser(t *testing.T)\n527: func TestRedisStore_ConnectionFailure(t *testing.T)\n528: func TestRedisStore_KeyExpiration(t *testing.T)\n529: ```\n530: \n531: **File**: `session/memory_store_test.go`\n532: \n533: ```go\n534: func TestMemoryStore_BasicOperations(t *testing.T)\n535: func TestMemoryStore_ListFiltering(t *testing.T)\n536: func TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n537: func TestMemoryStore_MemoryLimit(t *testing.T)\n538: ```\n539: \n540: **File**: `middleware/session_middleware_test.go`\n541: \n542: ```go\n543: func TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Cookie(t *testing.T)\n544: func TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Header(t *testing.T)\n545: func TestSessionMiddleware_AttachSession(t *testing.T)\n546: func TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_Success(t *testing.T)\n547: func TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_InvalidToken(t *testing.T)\n548: ```\n549: \n550: ### Test Fixtures\n551: \n552: ```go\n553: func newTestSession(id, namespace, backendName, userID string) *Session {\n554:     return &Session{\n555:         ID:             id,\n556:         Namespace:      namespace,\n557:         Kind:           \"AgentRuntime\",\n558:         BackendName:    backendName,\n559:         BackendURL:     \"http://backend:8080\",\n560:         UserID:         userID,\n561:         CreatedAt:      time.Now(),\n562:         LastActivityAt: time.Now(),\n563:         ExpiresAt:      time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n564:         State:          SessionStateActive,\n565:     }\n566: }\n567: \n568: func newTestSessionConfig() *SessionConfig {\n569:     return &SessionConfig{\n570:         Enabled:         true,\n571:         CookieName:      \"agentcube_session\",\n572:         TokenHeader:     \"X-AgentCube-Session\",\n573:         MaxDuration:     8 * time.Hour,\n574:         IdleTimeout:     15 * time.Minute,\n575:         CleanupInterval: 1 * time.Minute,\n576:         StoreType:       \"memory\",\n577:     }\n578: }\n579: \n580: func newTestRedisConfig(addr, password string) *RedisSessionConfig {\n581:     return &RedisSessionConfig{\n582:         Addr:         addr,\n583:         Password:     password,\n584:         DB:           0,\n585:         KeyPrefix:    \"agentcube:session:\",\n586:         PoolSize:     10,\n587:         DialTimeout:  5 * time.Second,\n588:         ReadTimeout:  3 * time.Second,\n589:         WriteTimeout: 3 * time.Second,\n590:     }\n591: }\n592: ```\n593: \n594: ### Mock Setup\n595: \n596: ```go\n597: // Mock session store for testing\n598: type MockSessionStore struct {\n599:     sessions sync.Map\n600:     mu       sync.Mutex\n601: }\n602: \n603: func (m *MockSessionStore) Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error) {\n604:     if v, ok := m.sessions.Load(id); ok {\n605:         return v.(*Session), nil\n606:     }\n607:     return nil, ErrSessionNotFound\n608: }\n609: \n610: func (m *MockSessionStore) Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error {\n611:     m.sessions.Store(session.ID, session)\n612:     return nil\n613: }\n614: \n615: // Mock Redis server for integration tests\n616: func newMockRedisServer() *miniredis.Miniredis {\n617:     mr, _ := miniredis.Run()\n618:     return mr\n619: }\n620: ```\n621: \n622: ### Integration Tests\n623: \n624: **File**: `session/session_integration_test.go`\n625: \n626: ```go\n627: // Test scenarios (requires Redis):\n628: func TestSessionManager_RedisPersistence(t *testing.T)\n629: func TestSessionManager_SessionExpiration(t *testing.T)\n630: func TestSessionManager_ConcurrentSessionAccess(t *testing.T)\n631: func TestSessionManager_CleanupRoutine(t *testing.T)\n632: func TestSessionManager_Failover(t *testing.T)\n633: ```\n634: \n635: ### Performance Tests\n636: \n637: ```go\n638: func BenchmarkSessionManager_CreateSession(b *testing.B)\n639: func BenchmarkSessionManager_GetSession(b *testing.B)\n640: func BenchmarkSessionStore_Redis(b *testing.B)\n641: func BenchmarkSessionStore_Memory(b *testing.B)\n642: ```\n643: \n644: ### Coverage Requirements\n645: \n646: - Session manager: 100%\n647: - Session store implementations: 100%\n648: - Middleware: 100%\n649: - Error handling paths: 100%\n650: - Overall: ≥85%\n651: \n652: ## Implementation Notes\n653: \n654: ### Session ID Generation\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func GenerateSessionID() string {\n658:     // Format: sess_<timestamp>_<random>\n659:     // Example: sess_1699000000_abc123def456\n660:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"sess_%d_%s\", \n661:         time.Now().UnixNano(),\n662:         base64.RawURLEncoding.EncodeToString(randomBytes(16)),\n663:     )\n664: }\n665: ```\n666: \n667: ### Redis Key Schema\n668: \n669: ```\n670: # Session data (with TTL)\n671: agentcube:session:{session-id} = JSON(session)\n672: \n673: # User session index (Set)\n674: agentcube:user:{user-id}:sessions = {session-id-1, session-id-2, ...}\n675: \n676: # Backend session index (Set)\n677: agentcube:backend:{namespace}:{kind}:{name}:sessions = {session-id-1, ...}\n678: \n679: # Active sessions counter\n680: agentcube:stats:active_sessions = {count}\n681: ```\n682: \n683: ### Session Cleanup Strategy\n684: \n685: ```go\n686: // Background cleanup routine\n687: func (m *SessionManager) cleanupLoop(ctx context.Context) {\n688:     ticker := time.NewTicker(m.config.CleanupInterval)\n689:     defer ticker.Stop()\n690:     \n691:     for {\n692:         select {\n693:         case <-ctx.Done():\n694:             return\n695:         case <-ticker.C:\n696:             expired, err := m.CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx)\n697:             if err != nil {\n698:                 m.metrics.ErrorsTotal.Inc()\n699:             }\n700:             m.metrics.SessionsExpired.Add(float64(expired))\n701:         }\n702:     }\n703: }\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ### Session Affinity Algorithm\n707: \n708: ```go\n709: func (r *Resolver) resolveWithAffinity(\n710:     session *Session,\n711:     availableBackends []*RouteEntry,\n712: ) (*RouteEntry, error) {\n713:     // Priority 1: Session's current backend (if healthy)\n714:     if session != nil {\n715:         for _, backend := range availableBackends {\n716:             if backend.Name == session.BackendName && backend.Health.Healthy {\n717:                 return backend, nil\n718:             }\n719:         }\n720:         // Current backend unhealthy - need to reassign\n721:     }\n722:     \n723:     // Priority 2: Least loaded healthy backend\n724:     return selectLeastLoaded(availableBackends), nil\n725: }\n726: ```\n727: \n728: ### Connection Pool Configuration\n729: \n730: ```go\n731: func NewRedisPool(config *RedisSessionConfig) *redis.Client {\n732:     return redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n733:         Addr:         config.Addr,\n734:         Password:     config.Password,\n735:         DB:           config.DB,\n736:         PoolSize:     config.PoolSize,\n737:         MinIdleConns: config.PoolSize / 2,\n738:         MaxConnAge:   24 * time.Hour,\n739:         DialTimeout:  config.DialTimeout,\n740:         ReadTimeout:  config.ReadTimeout,\n741:         WriteTimeout: config.WriteTimeout,\n742:         OnConnect: func(ctx context.Context, cn *redis.Conn) error {\n743:             log.Printf(\"Redis connection established: %v\", cn)\n744:             return nil\n745:         },\n746:     })\n747: }\n748: ```\n749: \n750: ### Graceful Shutdown\n751: \n752: ```go\n753: func (m *SessionManager) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n754:     // 1. Stop cleanup loop\n755:     close(m.stopCh)\n756:     \n757:     // 2. Wait for background tasks\n758:     done := make(chan struct{})\n759:     go func() {\n760:         m.wg.Wait()\n761:         close(done)\n762:     }()\n763:     \n764:     select {\n765:     case <-done:\n766:         // Cleanup completed\n767:     case <-ctx.Done():\n768:         return ctx.Err()\n769:     case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n770:         return errors.New(\"shutdown timeout\")\n771:     }\n772:     \n773:     // 3. Persist in-memory sessions (if using memory store)\n774:     if ms, ok := m.store.(*MemoryStore); ok {\n775:         if err := ms.Persist(ctx); err != nil {\n776:             log.Printf(\"Failed to persist sessions: %v\", err)\n777:         }\n778:     }\n779:     \n780:     // 4. Close store connection\n781:     return m.store.Close()\n782: }\n783: ```\n784: \n785: ### Metrics Exposure\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: // Prometheus metrics\n789: func (m *SessionManager) RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) {\n790:     m.metrics.ActiveSessions = prometheus.NewGauge(prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:         Name: \"agentcube_router_active_sessions\",\n792:         Help: \"Number of active sessions\",\n793:     })\n794:     \n795:     m.metrics.SessionsCreated = prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n796:         Name: \"agentcube_router_sessions_created_total\",\n797:         Help: \"Total number of sessions created\",\n798:     })\n799:     \n800:     m.metrics.SessionDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n801:         Name:    \"agentcube_router_session_duration_seconds\",\n802:         Help:    \"Session duration in seconds\",\n803:         Buckets: prometheus.ExponentialBuckets(60, 2, 10),\n804:     })\n805:     \n806:     reg.MustRegister(\n807:         m.metrics.ActiveSessions,\n808:         m.metrics.SessionsCreated,\n809:         m.metrics.SessionsExpired,\n810:         m.metrics.SessionsTerminated,\n811:         m.metrics.SessionDuration,\n812:         m.metrics.StoreLatency,\n813:     )\n814: }\n815: ```\n816: \n817: ### Configuration Example\n818: \n819: ```yaml\n820: # Helm values.yaml\n821: router:\n822:   session:\n823:     enabled: true\n824:     cookieName: agentcube_session\n825:     maxDuration: 8h\n826:     idleTimeout: 15m\n827:     cleanupInterval: 1m\n828:     store:\n829:       type: redis\n830:       redis:\n831:         addr: redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\n832:         password: \"\"\n833:         db: 0\n834:         keyPrefix: \"agentcube:session:\"\n835:         poolSize: 10\n836: ```\n837: \n838: ### Environment Variables\n839: \n840: ```bash\n841: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_ENABLED=true\n842: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_COOKIE_NAME=agentcube_session\n843: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_MAX_DURATION=8h\n844: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_IDLE_TIMEOUT=15m\n845: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=1m\n846: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_STORE_TYPE=redis\n847: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_ADDR=redis:6379\n848: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_PASSWORD=\n849: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_DB=0\n850: ```\n\n(End of file - total 850 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Session Creation**: Create a new session when a client makes the first request to a backend\n2. **Session Tracking**: Track active sessions per backend (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n3. **Session Binding**: Bind client requests to specific backend instances based on session affinity\n4. **Session Timeout**: Enforce session timeout policies (idle timeout, max duration)\n5. **Session Cleanup**: Clean up expired or abandoned sessions\n6. **Session Metrics**: Expose metrics for active sessions, session creation rate, etc.\n\n### Non-Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Performance**: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md","time":{"start":1775850898224,"end":1775850898248}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850898253,"sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","part":{"id":"prt_d78f6391b001F1wADps1ZerL6Z","messageID":"msg_d78f62898001Eo556jQCCue6l3","sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ad6efeee32134fa0aaa99368","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010: Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal defines the session management implementation for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The session management system is responsible for:\n6: \n7: 1. **Session lifecycle management** - Create, retrieve, update, and delete session records\n8: 2. **Session-aware routing** - Route requests to appropriate sandbox backends based on session affinity\n9: 3. **Session storage integration** - Persist session state in Redis-backed store for durability\n10: 4. **Activity tracking** - Update session last-activity timestamps for idle cleanup\n11: 5. **Workload manager coordination** - Create new sessions via workload manager when needed\n12: \n13: The session management system enables stateful communication with agent runtimes and code interpreters, ensuring that related requests are routed to the same sandbox instance.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** M\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Session Manager** (`pkg/router/session/manager.go`)\n24:    - `SessionManager` interface definition\n25:    - Session resolution from `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n26:    - Session creation via workload manager integration\n27:    - Session caching with in-memory LRU cache\n28:    - Activity timestamp updates\n29: \n30: 2. **Session Storage Interface** (`pkg/router/session/store.go`)\n31:    - Integration with existing `pkg/store` module\n32:    - `GetSandboxBySessionID` wrapper\n33:    - `UpdateSandboxLastActivity` wrapper\n34:    - Error handling and mapping\n35: \n36: 3. **Session Routing Logic** (`pkg/router/session/resolver.go`)\n37:    - Session-aware route resolution\n38:    - Fallback to session creation when header missing\n39:    - Session ID generation for new sessions\n40: \n41: 4. **Session Middleware** (`pkg/router/middleware/session.go`)\n42:    - Extract session ID from request headers\n43:    - Inject session context into request\n44:    - Update activity on successful invocation\n45: \n46: 5. **Session Types & Constants** (`pkg/router/session/types.go`)\n47:    - `SessionInfo` struct\n48:    - Session-related error types\n49:    - Header constants (`X-AgentCube-Session-ID`)\n50: \n51: ### Out of Scope\n52: \n53: - Session store implementation (uses existing `pkg/store` module)\n54: - Workload manager reconciler logic (separate controller component)\n55: - Session idle cleanup controller (agentd component)\n56: - WebSocket session management (deferred to future AR)\n57: - Cross-region session replication (deferred to future AR)\n58: \n59: ## Impact Analysis\n60: \n61: ### Dependencies\n62: \n63: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n64: |------------|------|--------|\n65: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Required | Session store interface |\n66: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Required | Session creation API |\n67: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Kubernetes client for WM calls |\n68: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Required | Redis client (via pkg/store) |\n69: | `github.com/google/uuid` | Required | Session ID generation |\n70: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | REST client for WM API |\n71: \n72: ### Downstream Consumers\n73: \n74: 1. **HTTP Handlers** - Invocation handlers depend on session manager for route resolution\n75: 2. **Middleware Stack** - Session middleware wraps handlers with session context\n76: 3. **Health Checker** - Session manager readiness affects `/health/ready` endpoint\n77: 4. **Activity Tracker** - Background goroutine updates session timestamps\n78: \n79: ### Backward Compatibility\n80: \n81: **Breaking Changes:** None - This is a new feature addition.\n82: \n83: **Behavioral Changes:**\n84: - Requests without session ID will trigger session creation (new behavior)\n85: - Session affinity enforced for all routed requests\n86: - Additional latency for session creation path (~10-50ms)\n87: \n88: ### Performance Impact\n89: \n90: - **Memory:** In-memory session cache (~100 bytes per active session)\n91: - **CPU:** Minimal - hash lookups and timestamp updates\n92: - **Network:** One WM API call per new session (create)\n93: - **Storage:** One Redis GET/PUT per session creation/update\n94: \n95: ## Alternatives Considered\n96: \n97: ### Alternative 1: Stateless Routing\n98: \n99: Route each request independently without session affinity.\n100: \n101: **Pros:**\n102: - Simpler implementation\n103: - No session state management overhead\n104: - Better load distribution across replicas\n105: \n106: **Cons:**\n107: - No stateful communication support\n108: - Each request may hit different sandbox instance\n109: - Breaks agent runtime execution continuity\n110: \n111: **Decision:** Rejected. Agent runtimes require stateful sessions for multi-turn conversations and execution context preservation.\n112: \n113: ### Alternative 2: Client-Side Session Management\n114: \n115: Delegate session management to clients; router only forwards session ID.\n116: \n117: **Pros:**\n118: - Simpler router implementation\n119: - Clients have full control over session lifecycle\n120: - No server-side session state\n121: \n122: **Cons:**\n123: - Clients must track session IDs manually\n124: - No server-side visibility into session usage\n125: - Cannot enforce idle cleanup policies\n126: - Harder to implement session-level metrics\n127: \n128: **Decision:** Rejected. Server-side session management provides better observability, cleanup, and lifecycle control.\n129: \n130: ### Alternative 3: In-Memory Session Store Only\n131: \n132: Store all session state in router memory without Redis persistence.\n133: \n134: **Pros:**\n135: - Fastest possible session lookups\n136: - No external dependency on Redis\n137: - Simpler deployment\n138: \n139: **Cons:**\n140: - Sessions lost on router restart\n141: - No horizontal scaling (sessions not shared across replicas)\n142: - Memory pressure from accumulated sessions\n143: - Cannot survive pod rescheduling\n144: \n145: **Decision:** Rejected. Redis-backed store provides durability and enables horizontal scaling.\n146: \n147: ### Alternative 4: Sidecar Session Manager\n148: \n149: Deploy session manager as a separate sidecar container alongside router.\n150: \n151: **Pros:**\n152: - Separation of concerns\n153: - Independent scaling of session manager\n154: - Can be shared across multiple routers\n155: \n156: **Cons:**\n157: - Increased deployment complexity\n158: - Additional network hop for session lookups\n159: - More moving parts to manage\n160: \n161: **Decision:** Rejected. Embedded session manager reduces latency and complexity for current project size.\n162: \n163: ## Design\n164: \n165: ### Architecture\n166: \n167: ```\n168: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n169: │                      HTTP Request                           │\n170: │            x-agentcube-session-id: sess-abc123              │\n171: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n172:                             │\n173:                             ▼\n174: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n175: │                    Session Middleware                       │\n176: │  - Extract session ID from header                           │\n177: │  - Inject into request context                              │\n178: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n179:                             │\n180:                             ▼\n181: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n182: │                   Session Manager                           │\n183: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n184: │  │  In-Memory Cache (LRU)                               │  │\n185: │  │  - sess-abc123 → SandboxInfo                         │  │\n186: │  │  - sess-def456 → SandboxInfo                         │  │\n187: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n188: │                            │                                │\n189: │                            │ Cache Miss                     │\n190: │                            ▼                                │\n191: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n192: │  │  Session Store (Redis via pkg/store)                 │  │\n193: │  │  - GetSandboxBySessionID(sess-abc123)                │  │\n194: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n195: │                            │                                │\n196: │                            │ Session Not Found              │\n197: │                            ▼                                │\n198: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n199: │  │  Workload Manager API                                │  │\n200: │  │  - POST /api/v1/sessions                             │  │\n201: │  │  - Returns: new SandboxInfo                          │  │\n202: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n203: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n204:                             │\n205:                             │ Returns SandboxInfo\n206:                             ▼\n207: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n208: │                      Route Resolver                         │\n209: │  - Resolve backend URL from SandboxInfo                     │\n210: │  - Check health status                                      │\n211: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n212:                             │\n213:                             ▼\n214: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n215: │                   Reverse Proxy                             │\n216: │  - Forward request to sandbox backend                       │\n217: │  - Inject JWT authentication                                │\n218: │  - Update session last-activity on success                  │\n219: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n220: ```\n221: \n222: ### Session Lifecycle\n223: \n224: ```\n225: ┌──────────┐     Create       ┌──────────┐     Update        ┌──────────┐\n226: │  Client  │ ───────────────► │  Router  │ ────────────────► │  Store   │\n227: │          │                  │          │                   │ (Redis)  │\n228: └──────────┘                  └──────────┘                   └──────────┘\n229:      │                            │                              │\n230:      │ 1. Request (no session ID) │                              │\n231:      │───────────────────────────►│                              │\n232:      │                            │                              │\n233:      │                            │ 2. Generate session ID       │\n234:      │                            │ 3. Call Workload Manager     │\n235:      │                            │─────────────────────────────►│\n236:      │                            │    Create session record     │\n237:      │                            │◄─────────────────────────────│\n238:      │                            │    Returns SandboxInfo       │\n239:      │                            │                              │\n240:      │                            │ 4. Cache in memory           │\n241:      │                            │                              │\n242:      │ 5. Response + Session ID   │                              │\n243:      │◄───────────────────────────│                              │\n244:      │                            │                              │\n245:      │                            │                              │\n246:      │ 6. Request (with session)  │                              │\n247:      │───────────────────────────►│                              │\n248:      │                            │                              │\n249:      │                            │ 7. Cache lookup              │\n250:      │                            │ 8. Update last-activity      │\n251:      │                            │─────────────────────────────►│\n252:      │                            │                              │\n253:      │ 9. Response                │                              │\n254:      │◄───────────────────────────│                              │\n255:      │                            │                              │\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### Data Structures\n259: \n260: ```go\n261: // SessionInfo represents session metadata\n262: type SessionInfo struct {\n263:     SessionID     string            `json:\"sessionId\"`\n264:     Namespace     string            `json:\"namespace\"`\n265:     ResourceType  string            `json:\"resourceType\"` // agentruntime or codeinterpreter\n266:     ResourceName  string            `json:\"resourceName\"`\n267:     SandboxID     string            `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n268:     BackendURL    string            `json:\"backendUrl\"`\n269:     CreatedAt     time.Time         `json:\"createdAt\"`\n270:     LastActivity  time.Time         `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n271:     Labels        map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n272: }\n273: \n274: // SessionManager handles session lifecycle operations\n275: type SessionManager interface {\n276:     // GetOrResolve retrieves existing session or creates new one\n277:     GetOrResolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace, resourceType string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n278:     \n279:     // Get retrieves existing session from cache or store\n280:     Get(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n281:     \n282:     // Create creates a new session via workload manager\n283:     Create(ctx context.Context, namespace, resourceType, resourceName string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n284:     \n285:     // UpdateActivity updates last-activity timestamp\n286:     UpdateActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n287:     \n288:     // Delete removes session from cache and store\n289:     Delete(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n290: }\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ### API Integration\n294: \n295: **Workload Manager Session Creation:**\n296: \n297: ```go\n298: POST /api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sessions\n299: Content-Type: application/json\n300: \n301: {\n302:   \"resourceType\": \"agentruntime\",\n303:   \"resourceName\": \"my-agent\",\n304:   \"sandboxSpec\": {\n305:     \"cpu\": \"100m\",\n306:     \"memory\": \"128Mi\"\n307:   }\n308: }\n309: \n310: Response 201 Created:\n311: {\n312:   \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc123\",\n313:   \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-xyz789\",\n314:   \"backendUrl\": \"http://sandbox-xyz789.default.svc.cluster.local:8080\",\n315:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\"\n316: }\n317: ```\n318: \n319: ### Error Handling\n320: \n321: | Error | HTTP Code | Response | Handling |\n322: |-------|-----------|----------|----------|\n323: | Session ID missing, auto-create fails | 503 | `{\"error\": \"failed to create session\", \"reason\": \"...\"}` | Return error, no fallback |\n324: | Session not found in store | 404 | `{\"error\": \"session not found\", \"sessionId\": \"...\"}` | Client must create new session |\n325: | Workload Manager unavailable | 503 | `{\"error\": \"workload manager unavailable\"}` | Circuit breaker, cached fallback |\n326: | Redis store unavailable | 500 | `{\"error\": \"session store unavailable\"}` | Degrade to in-memory only |\n327: | Session creation timeout | 504 | `{\"error\": \"session creation timeout\"}` | Retry with backoff (max 3) |\n328: \n329: ## Implementation Plan\n330: \n331: ### Phase 1: Session Manager Core (3 days)\n332: \n333: 1. Define `SessionManager` interface\n334: 2. Implement in-memory cache with LRU eviction\n335: 3. Integrate with `pkg/store` for Redis persistence\n336: 4. Add session ID generation utility\n337: \n338: ### Phase 2: Workload Manager Integration (2 days)\n339: \n340: 1. Implement WM client for session creation\n341: 2. Add retry logic with exponential backoff\n342: 3. Handle WM errors gracefully\n343: 4. Write unit tests for WM integration\n344: \n345: ### Phase 3: Routing Integration (2 days)\n346: \n347: 1. Modify `Resolver` to use session manager\n348: 2. Add session-aware route resolution\n349: 3. Update middleware stack with session handling\n350: 4. Add activity tracking on successful invokes\n351: \n352: ### Phase 4: Testing & Documentation (2 days)\n353: \n354: 1. Write unit tests for session manager\n355: 2. Add integration tests with mock Redis\n356: 3. Document session management API\n357: 4. Update existing router tests\n358: \n359: ## Testing Strategy\n360: \n361: ### Unit Tests\n362: \n363: 1. **Session Manager Tests**\n364:    - `TestSessionManager_Get_CacheHit`\n365:    - `TestSessionManager_Get_CacheMiss_StoreHit`\n366:    - `TestSessionManager_Get_NotFound`\n367:    - `TestSessionManager_Create_Success`\n368:    - `TestSessionManager_Create_WMError`\n369:    - `TestSessionManager_UpdateActivity`\n370:    - `TestSessionManager_Delete`\n371:    - `TestSessionManager_LRU_Eviction`\n372: \n373: 2. **Session Resolver Tests**\n374:    - `TestResolve_WithSessionHeader`\n375:    - `TestResolve_WithoutSessionHeader_AutoCreate`\n376:    - `TestResolve_InvalidSessionID`\n377:    - `TestResolve_SessionWithoutBackend`\n378: \n379: 3. **Middleware Tests**\n380:    - `TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractHeader`\n381:    - `TestSessionMiddleware_InjectContext`\n382:    - `TestSessionMiddleware_UpdateActivity`\n383: \n384: ### Integration Tests\n385: \n386: 1. **End-to-End Session Flow**\n387:    - Create session via first request\n388:    - Reuse session for multiple requests\n389:    - Verify activity timestamp updates\n390:    - Test session expiration\n391: \n392: 2. **Failure Scenarios**\n393:    - Redis unavailable → graceful degradation\n394:    - WM unavailable → circuit breaker\n395:    - Network timeout → retry logic\n396: \n397: ## Future Considerations\n398: \n399: 1. **WebSocket Support** - Extend session management for WebSocket connections\n400: 2. **Session Affinity** - Support sticky sessions for multi-replica deployments\n401: 3. **Rate Limiting** - Per-session rate limiting beyond global concurrency\n402: 4. **Session Metrics** - Expose session count, creation rate, eviction rate\n403: 5. **Cross-Region Sessions** - Session replication for multi-region deployments\n404: 6. **Session Events** - Emit events for session lifecycle (create, update, delete)\n405: \n406: ## References\n407: \n408: - AR-009: Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core (`changes/AR-009/proposal.md`)\n409: - AR-008: Session Store Implementation (`changes/AR-008/`)\n410: - Session Routing Spec: `session-routing/spec.md`\n411: - Workload Manager Proposal: `pkg/workloadmanager/proposal.md`\n\n(End of file - total 411 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010: Router 会话管理\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines the session management implementation for the `pkg/router` module in the AgentCube project. The session management system is responsible for:\n\n1. **Session lifecycle management** - Create, retrieve, update, and delete session records\n2. **Session-aware routing** - Route requests to appropriate sandbox backends based on session affinity\n3. **Session storage integration** - Persist session state in Redis-backed store for durability\n4. **Activity tracking** - Update session last-activity timestamps for idle cleanup\n5. **Workload manager coordination** - Create new sessions via workload manager when needed\n\nThe session management system enables stateful communication with agent runtimes and code interpreters, ensuring that related requests are routed to the same sandbox instance.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775850898227,"end":1775850898251}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850898257,"sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","part":{"id":"prt_d78f63e2c0015II9vE6yUPe4qV","messageID":"msg_d78f62898001Eo556jQCCue6l3","sessionID":"ses_28709eb33ffe4QxUWWcvbtz4rn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4ca8f49930234a40b6d8fd78","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-010 — Router 会话管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Session Data Structures\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/router/session/types.go`\n20:   - Define `Session` struct with fields: `ID`, `Namespace`, `Kind`, `BackendName`, `BackendURL`, `UserID`, `CreatedAt`, `LastActivityAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `State`, `Metadata`, `mu`\n21:   - Define `SessionState` type with consts: `SessionStateActive`, `SessionStateIdle`, `SessionStateExpired`, `SessionStateTerminated`\n22:   - Define `SessionConfig` struct with all configuration fields\n23:   - Define `RedisSessionConfig` struct\n24:   - Add `GenerateSessionID()` helper function\n25: \n26: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Create `pkg/router/session/config.go`\n27:   - Implement `DefaultSessionConfig()` function\n28:   - Implement config validation method `Validate()`\n29:   - Implement environment variable loading\n30: \n31: ### Phase 2: Session Store Interface\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/router/session/store.go`\n34:   - Define `SessionStore` interface with methods: `Get()`, `Set()`, `Delete()`, `List()`, `ListByUser()`, `Close()`\n35:   - Define error types: `ErrSessionNotFound`, `ErrSessionStoreError`\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Create `pkg/router/session/memory_store.go`\n38:   - Implement `MemoryStore` struct with `sync.Map` and `sync.RWMutex`\n39:   - Implement all `SessionStore` interface methods\n40:   - Implement thread-safe concurrent access\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Create `pkg/router/session/redis_store.go`\n43:   - Implement `RedisStore` struct with redis client and config\n44:   - Implement `NewRedisStore()` constructor\n45:   - Implement all `SessionStore` interface methods\n46:   - Implement Redis key schema per design spec\n47:   - Implement connection pool configuration\n48: \n49: ### Phase 3: Session Manager\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/router/session/manager.go`\n52:   - Define `SessionManager` struct with fields: `config`, `store`, `metrics`, `stopCh`, `wg`, `mu`\n53:   - Define `SessionMetrics` struct with Prometheus metrics\n54: \n55: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewSessionManager()` constructor\n56:   - Takes config and store\n57:   - Creates metrics\n58:   - Returns initialized *SessionManager\n59: \n60: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `SessionManager.CreateSession()` method\n61:   - Creates new session with provided parameters\n62:   - Generates session ID\n63:   - Stores session in store\n64:   - Records metrics\n65:   - Returns *Session or error\n66: \n67: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `SessionManager.GetSession()` method\n68:   - Retrieves session from store by ID\n69:   - Checks expiration\n70:   - Updates last activity timestamp\n71:   - Returns *Session or error\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `SessionManager.UpdateSession()` method\n74:   - Updates session metadata\n75:   - Stores updated session\n76: \n77: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `SessionManager.DeleteSession()` method\n78:   - Terminates session\n79:   - Removes from store\n80:   - Records metrics\n81: \n82: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `SessionManager.ListSessions()` method\n83:   - Lists sessions matching filters\n84:   - Supports namespace, kind, userID filters\n85: \n86: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `SessionManager.CleanupExpiredSessions()` method\n87:   - Scans for expired sessions\n88:   - Removes expired sessions\n89:   - Returns count of cleaned sessions\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `SessionManager.Start()` method\n92:   - Starts background cleanup loop\n93:   - Runs initial cleanup\n94: \n95: - [ ] **TASK-029**: Implement `SessionManager.Shutdown()` method\n96:   - Stops cleanup loop\n97:   - Waits for background tasks\n98:   - Persists in-memory sessions (if using memory store)\n99:   - Closes store connection\n100: \n101: ### Phase 4: Session Middleware\n102: \n103: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/router/middleware/session_middleware.go`\n104:   - Define `SessionMiddleware` struct with manager and config\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.ExtractSession()` method\n107:   - Extracts session token from cookie\n108:   - Falls back to header if cookie not present\n109:   - Returns session ID or error\n110: \n111: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.AttachSession()` method\n112:   - Sets session cookie on response\n113:   - Configures cookie properties (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite)\n114: \n115: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.WithSession()` method\n116:   - Wraps HTTP handler with session context\n117:   - Validates session token\n118:   - Attaches session to request context\n119: \n120: ### Phase 5: Session Integration with Router\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/router/session_resolver.go`\n123:   - Implement `ResolveWithSession()` method\n124:   - Check session affinity\n125:   - Reassign backend if unhealthy\n126:   - Update session last activity\n127: \n128: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement session affinity algorithm\n129:   - Priority 1: Session's current backend (if healthy)\n130:   - Priority 2: Least loaded healthy backend\n131: \n132: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Update `pkg/router/handler.go`\n133:   - Integrate session middleware\n134:   - Pass session to resolver\n135: \n136: ### Phase 6: Session Management Endpoints\n137: \n138: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Create `pkg/router/session_handler.go`\n139:   - Define `SessionHandler` struct\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement session management HTTP handlers\n142:   - `ListSessionsHandler()` - GET /sessions\n143:   - `GetSessionHandler()` - GET /sessions/{id}\n144:   - `CreateSessionHandler()` - POST /sessions\n145:   - `DeleteSessionHandler()` - DELETE /sessions/{id}\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement error response format\n148:   - Define `SessionErrorResponse` struct\n149:   - Define error codes constants\n150: \n151: ### Phase 7: Error Handling\n152: \n153: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Create `pkg/router/session_errors.go`\n154:   - Define session error types:\n155:     - `ErrSessionNotFound`, `ErrSessionExpired`, `ErrSessionTerminated`\n156:     - `ErrSessionCreateFailed`, `ErrSessionStoreError`\n157:     - `ErrBackendUnavailable`, `ErrAffinityBroken`\n158:     - `ErrInvalidSessionConfig`, `ErrRedisConnectionFailed`\n159:   - Define error codes constants\n160: \n161: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement fallback strategy\n162:   - Define `FallbackStrategy` type\n163:   - Implement graceful degradation logic\n164: \n165: ### Phase 8: Testing (TDD)\n166: \n167: #### Unit Tests - Session Types\n168: \n169: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestSession_IsExpired` in `pkg/router/session/session_test.go`\n170:   - Given: Session with ExpiresAt in the past\n171:   - When: IsExpired() called\n172:   - Then: Returns true\n173: \n174: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestSession_IsIdle`\n175:   - Given: Session with LastActivityAt exceeding idle timeout\n176:   - When: IsIdle() called\n177:   - Then: Returns true\n178: \n179: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestSession_UpdateActivity`\n180:   - Given: Active session\n181:   - When: UpdateActivity() called\n182:   - Then: LastActivityAt updated to now\n183: \n1